Sentencas: A two-dimensional (2D) EIS simulation approach is developed by solving a SOFC unit cell model with imposed sinusoidal voltage perturbations at different frequencies.
Titulo: Direct two-dimensional electrochemical impedance spectra simulation for solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The transient SOFC unit cell model describes the intricate interdependency among the ionic/electronic conduction, multi-component species transport, electrochemical reaction processes and electrode microstructure as well as the coupling processes of mass, energy, momentum transport within flow channels.
Titulo: Direct two-dimensional electrochemical impedance spectra simulation for solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The model calculates the local transient response and impedance spectra as a function of channel position.
Titulo: Direct two-dimensional electrochemical impedance spectra simulation for solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The effects of the reaction depletion, product accumulation as well as the temperature variation along the flow channels on the EIS spectra are numerically simulated with a counter-flow mode.
Titulo: Direct two-dimensional electrochemical impedance spectra simulation for solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The results show that the convection-diffusion process along the flow channel has significant effects on the low frequency half circle of the impedance spectra.
Titulo: Direct two-dimensional electrochemical impedance spectra simulation for solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The temperature oscillations accumulate along the flow channels, and then affect the current responses which probably lead to an electro-thermal impedance effects.
Titulo: Direct two-dimensional electrochemical impedance spectra simulation for solid oxide fuel cell
